Document.document: I found that when changing databases from within psql the prompt went sort of strange. bash$ psql disks Welcome to the POSTGRESQL interactive sql monitor: Please read the file COPYRIGHT for copyright terms of POSTGRESQL type BACKSLASH? for help on slash commands type BACKSLASHq to quit type BACKSLASHg or terminate with semicolon to execute query You are currently connected to the database: disks disks=> BACKSLASHc postgres closing connection to database: disks connecting to new database: postgres postgres== BACKSLASHc disks closing connection to database: postgres connecting to new database: disks disks== BACKSLASHq bash$ Note the => changes to == after a connect and stays that way on subsequent database changes. Submitted by: Keith Parks <emkxp01@mtcc.demon.co.uk>

Document.document: Here's the final set of patches to 6.0 (sup'd on 27/12/96) that allow a full gmake of the code without interruption. There's also some tidy-up of the MAXPATHLEN stuff based on the assumption that all supported platforms have MAXPATHLEN defined in <sys/param.h>. (The only unknowns for the above are AIX and IRIX5.)
